{% comment %} WHAT'S NEW TAB FOR CHANGES COMPARED TO THE LAST VERSION {% endcomment %}
{% capture whatsnew %}
	<h4 class="body-font whatsnew-headline">What&rsquo;s new since v1.0.0</h4>

	This version changed:
		<code class="classes">CSS/LESS</code>
	but not:
		<code class="classes">HTML</code>,
		<code class="classes">JS</code>

	<ul class="lists">
		<li>
			The text inside the selects had just enough space so you could read them comfortably. Unless the text included a descender or ascender. In that case
			it would have been just a bit uncomfortable as you had to guess some parts of the letter. No more guessing.
			(<a href="https://github.com/WestpacCXTeam/GUI-source/issues/139" target="_blank">#139</a>)
		</li>
	</ul>
{{ whatsnew }}{% endcapture %}


